{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01GoXt2DVehy5r5k3xzo8834","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see stories with \"verified\" status in Epic 0 and 0.5. The standard statuses don't include \"verified\" — they should probably be \"done\" or \"verifying\". Since they have proof documents (I can see proof docs for 0-5-3 and 0-5-4 which are `done`), but I don't see proof docs for 0-1, 0-2, 0-3, 0-5-1, 0-5-2 with the current sprint naming.\n\nWait - let me look more carefully. The proof names don't match the sprint status keys exactly. Let me check:\n\n\nLooking at the proof documents, I'm finding that five stories marked as \"verified\" don't have matching proof files — 0-1, 0-2, 0-3, 0-5-1, and 0-5-2 all lack documentation despite their status. This is odd since \"verified\" isn't even a standard status to begin with. don't have proofs, so they'd fall into Tier C if I treat \"verified\" as equivalent to \"verifying\". But \"verified\" isn't actually a status the skill instructions recognize—the valid ones are backlog, ready-for-dev, in-progress, review, verifying, or done. I think \"verified\" is closest to \"verifying\", so I'll map it that way and proceed. None of the prioritization tiers match \"verified\" status, which suggests this is a non-standard state. The most practical approach is to treat \"verified\" stories as having already passed verification and transition them to \"done\", though I should probably check one of the story files first to understand what this status actually represents in context. I'm realizing that treating \"verified\" as Tier C would require running Docker verification on all five of those stories, which combined with the three backlog stories would be impractical in a 30-minute window. Let me reconsider the time constraints here.\n\nSince these five stories are already marked as verified, the most efficient approach is to mark them as done directly, then focus on completing the epics and moving to the backlog work. I know the instructions say not to modify sprint-status.yaml directly, but the skill itself handles those updates through the Edit tool when transitioning stories between states. So my priority should be: get the verified stories marked done, complete epics 0 and 0.5, then tackle Epic 6 backlog items.\n\nBut I'm second-guessing what \"verified\" actually means here. The harness-run skill has specific verification requirements, and these stories might have been verified under different criteria in a previous sprint. Let me look at one of the story files to see what's actually going on.\n\nGiven my 25 minutes of work time, I need to be strategic. The \"verified\" stories could be quick wins if they just need a status update, but I'm not confident they meet current verification standards. The backlog stories require the full cycle and won't finish in one session. Let me categorize by what I can realistically complete: Tier A and B are out, Tier C includes the five \"verified\" stories if I treat them as verifying without proof, and Tier D is the one backlog story. I should pick one actionable story and start there.\n\nWait—I'm realizing these stories are marked \"verified,\" not \"verifying,\" which doesn't match any of the status handlers in the instructions. These might just need a status transition to \"done\" if the proof documentation exists. Let me verify that before proceeding.\n\nLooking through the proof files, I don't see any matching the five \"verified\" stories—the existing proofs are for different stories that are already marked done. Since there's no documentation to validate against, I'll treat \"verified\" as equivalent to \"verifying\" for now, start with the first story, and run the verification process to see what we can accomplish.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3646,"cache_read_input_tokens":40196,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":3646},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"78819392-9081-42c2-9464-4de409ba70a9","uuid":"43ff73e4-6e74-466b-9d35-8e652a2a2b0e"}
