{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_0131SJwPQhs5Jt3jNrXg5s2c","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The story file says `Status: review` but sprint-status.yaml says `verified`. The sprint-status.yaml is the source of truth for the harness-run process. But the story status says \"review\" which means code review hasn't been done yet.\n\nWait, the sprint-status says \"verified\" for this story. Let me re-read the sprint-status.yaml.\n\nActually, looking back at my earlier read of sprint-status.yaml:\n```\n0-2-ralph-progress-display: verified\n```\n\nBut the story file says `Status: review`. These are inconsistent. Since the story file says `review`, this story needs a code review first, not verification. \n\nIt's in Tier B, not Tier C. There's a conflict here—sprint-status.yaml shows `verified` while the story file says `review`. The harness-run instructions treat sprint-status.yaml as the source of truth, so I should consider this story as `verified` (equivalent to `verifying`), even though the story file hasn't been updated yet.\n\nThe discrepancy is worth noting since the story file suggests code review hasn't happened, but I'll follow the authoritative source and run Docker verification. If there are issues, the verification will surface them. Let me check if there are BATS tests for this ralph.sh change first.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1769,"cache_read_input_tokens":75002,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1769},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"78819392-9081-42c2-9464-4de409ba70a9","uuid":"c7f8ca3a-1d54-4f49-837a-25c3bc215146"}
