{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_013SgeSr4h6bsY6X2Sbj7t3i","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Verification Proof: Story 0.2 — Ralph Progress Display\n     2→\n     3→## AC 1: Progress polling prints structured update lines\n     4→\n     5→**Given** ralph polls `sprint-state.json` while Claude runs, **When** progress changes, **Then** ralph prints `[INFO] Story {key}: {phase} ({detail})`.\n     6→\n     7→```bash\n     8→docker exec codeharness-verify bash -c 'cat > /tmp/ac1-test.sh << '\\''SCRIPT'\\''\n     9→#!/usr/bin/env bash\n    10→cd /tmp && mkdir -p ac1-test && cd ac1-test\n    11→cat > sprint-state.json << JSONEOF\n    12→{\"run\":{\"currentStory\":\"1-1-init\",\"currentPhase\":\"development\",\"lastAction\":\"writing tests\",\"acProgress\":\"\"}}\n    13→JSONEOF\n    14→PREV_STORY=\"\" PREV_PHASE=\"\" PREV_AC_PROGRESS=\"\" PREV_LAST_ACTION=\"\"\n    15→log_status() { local level=$1 message=$2; [[ \"$level\" == \"DEBUG\" ]] && return; echo \"[$(date \"+%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S\")] [$level] $message\"; }\n    16→poll_sprint_state_progress() {\n    17→    local state_file=\"sprint-state.json\"; [[ -f \"$state_file\" ]] || return 0\n    18→    local raw; raw=$(jq -r \"[.run.currentStory // \\\"\\\", .run.currentPhase // \\\"\\\", .run.lastAction // \\\"\\\", .run.acProgress // \\\"\\\"] | join(\\\"\\\\t\\\")\" \"$state_file\" 2>/dev/null) || return 0\n    19→    [[ -n \"$raw\" ]] || return 0\n    20→    local cur_story cur_phase cur_action cur_ac; IFS=$'\"'\"'\\t'\"'\"' read -r cur_story cur_phase cur_action cur_ac <<< \"$raw\"\n    21→    [[ -z \"$cur_story\" ]] && return 0\n    22→    if [[ \"$cur_story\" != \"$PREV_STORY\" || \"$cur_phase\" != \"$PREV_PHASE\" ]]; then\n    23→        if [[ -n \"$cur_action\" && \"$cur_action\" != \"null\" ]]; then log_status \"INFO\" \"Story ${cur_story}: ${cur_phase} (${cur_action})\"; else log_status \"INFO\" \"Story ${cur_story}: ${cur_phase}\"; fi\n    24→    elif [[ \"$cur_ac\" != \"$PREV_AC_PROGRESS\" && -n \"$cur_ac\" && \"$cur_ac\" != \"null\" ]]; then log_status \"INFO\" \"Story ${cur_story}: verify (AC ${cur_ac})\"\n    25→    elif [[ \"$cur_action\" != \"$PREV_LAST_ACTION\" && -n \"$cur_action\" && \"$cur_action\" != \"null\" ]]; then log_status \"INFO\" \"Story ${cur_story}: ${cur_phase} (${cur_action})\"; fi\n    26→    PREV_STORY=\"$cur_story\"; PREV_PHASE=\"$cur_phase\"; PREV_AC_PROGRESS=\"$cur_ac\"; PREV_LAST_ACTION=\"$cur_action\"\n    27→}\n    28→echo \"=== First poll (new story) ===\"; poll_sprint_state_progress\n    29→echo \"\"; echo \"=== Second poll (same data - should be silent) ===\"; poll_sprint_state_progress\n    30→echo \"\"; echo \"=== Third poll (phase change to verify) ===\"\n    31→cat > sprint-state.json << JSONEOF2\n    32→{\"run\":{\"currentStory\":\"1-1-init\",\"currentPhase\":\"verify\",\"lastAction\":\"running AC checks\",\"acProgress\":\"\"}}\n    33→JSONEOF2\n    34→poll_sprint_state_progress\n    35→echo \"\"; echo \"=== Fourth poll (AC progress change) ===\"\n    36→cat > sprint-state.json << JSONEOF3\n    37→{\"run\":{\"currentStory\":\"1-1-init\",\"currentPhase\":\"verify\",\"lastAction\":\"running AC checks\",\"acProgress\":\"2/4\"}}\n    38→JSONEOF3\n    39→poll_sprint_state_progress\n    40→echo \"\"; echo \"=== Fifth poll (action change within same phase) ===\"\n    41→cat > sprint-state.json << JSONEOF4\n    42→{\"run\":{\"currentStory\":\"1-1-init\",\"currentPhase\":\"verify\",\"lastAction\":\"checking observability\",\"acProgress\":\"2/4\"}}\n    43→JSONEOF4\n    44→poll_sprint_state_progress\n    45→SCRIPT\n    46→chmod +x /tmp/ac1-test.sh && bash /tmp/ac1-test.sh'\n    47→```\n    48→\n    49→```output\n    50→=== First poll (new story) ===\n    51→[2026-03-21 08:00:41] [INFO] Story 1-1-init: development (writing tests)\n    52→\n    53→=== Second poll (same data - should be silent) ===\n    54→\n    55→=== Third poll (phase change to verify) ===\n    56→[2026-03-21 08:00:41] [INFO] Story 1-1-init: verify (running AC checks)\n    57→\n    58→=== Fourth poll (AC progress change) ===\n    59→[2026-03-21 08:00:41] [INFO] Story 1-1-init: verify (AC 2/4)\n    60→\n    61→=== Fifth poll (action change within same phase) ===\n    62→[2026-03-21 08:00:41] [INFO] Story 1-1-init: verify (checking observability)\n    63→```\n    64→\n    65→**Result: PASS** -- Format matches `[INFO] Story {key}: {phase} ({detail})`. Silent when no change. Detects story, phase, AC, and action changes independently.\n    66→\n    67→## AC 2: Iteration result prints completed/failed/blocked icons and next story\n    68→\n    69→**Given** an iteration completes, **When** ralph processes the result, **Then** it prints: completed stories (checkmark), failed stories (cross), blocked stories (saltire), and next story.\n    70→\n    71→```bash\n    72→docker exec codeharness-verify bash -c 'cat > /tmp/ac2-test.sh << '\\''SCRIPT'\\''\n    73→#!/usr/bin/env bash\n    74→cd /tmp && mkdir -p ac2-test && cd ac2-test\n    75→cat > sprint-status.yaml << YAMLEOF\n    76→1-1-init-project: done\n    77→1-2-add-auth: done\n    78→2-1-dashboard: in-progress\n    79→2-2-reports: pending\n    80→3-1-notifications: pending\n    81→YAMLEOF\n    82→cat > sprint-state.json << JSONEOF\n    83→{\"run\":{\"cost\":4.52,\"failed\":[\"1-3-broken-feature\"]}}\n    84→JSONEOF\n    85→echo \"2-3-blocked-story\" > .flagged_stories\n    86→SPRINT_STATUS_FILE=\"sprint-status.yaml\"; FLAGGED_STORIES_FILE=\".flagged_stories\"; loop_count=3; loop_start_time=$(($(date +%s) - 1825))\n    87→log_status() { local level=$1 message=$2; [[ \"$level\" == \"DEBUG\" ]] && return; echo \"[$(date \"+%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S\")] [$level] $message\"; }\n    88→get_task_counts() { local total=0 completed=0; while IFS=: read -r key value; do key=$(echo \"$key\" | sed \"s/^[[:space:]]*//;s/[[:space:]]*$//\"); value=$(echo \"$value\" | sed \"s/^[[:space:]]*//;s/[[:space:]]*$//\"); [[ -z \"$key\" || \"$key\" == \\#* ]] && continue; if [[ \"$key\" =~ ^[0-9]+-[0-9]+- ]]; then total=$((total + 1)); [[ \"$value\" == \"done\" ]] && completed=$((completed + 1)); fi; done < \"$SPRINT_STATUS_FILE\"; echo \"$total $completed\"; }\n    89→is_story_flagged() { [[ -f \"$FLAGGED_STORIES_FILE\" ]] && grep -qF \"$1\" \"$FLAGGED_STORIES_FILE\" 2>/dev/null; }\n    90→print_progress_summary() {\n    91→    local counts; counts=$(get_task_counts); local total=${counts%% *}; local completed=${counts##* }; local remaining=$((total - completed))\n    92→    local elapsed=$(( $(date +%s) - loop_start_time )); local elapsed_fmt\n    93→    if [[ $elapsed -ge 3600 ]]; then elapsed_fmt=\"$((elapsed / 3600))h$((elapsed % 3600 / 60))m\"; elif [[ $elapsed -ge 60 ]]; then elapsed_fmt=\"$((elapsed / 60))m$((elapsed % 60))s\"; else elapsed_fmt=\"${elapsed}s\"; fi\n    94→    local cost=\"\" cost_fmt=\"\" failed_stories=\"\"\n    95→    if [[ -f \"sprint-state.json\" ]]; then local state_data; state_data=$(jq -r \"(.run.cost // 0 | tostring) + \\\"\\\\n\\\" + ((.run.failed // []) | join(\\\"\\\\n\\\"))\" \"sprint-state.json\" 2>/dev/null) || state_data=\"\"; if [[ -n \"$state_data\" ]]; then cost=$(head -1 <<< \"$state_data\"); failed_stories=$(tail -n +2 <<< \"$state_data\"); if [[ -n \"$cost\" && \"$cost\" != \"0\" && \"$cost\" != \"null\" ]]; then cost_fmt=\", cost: \\$${cost}\"; fi; fi; fi\n    96→    log_status \"INFO\" \"Progress: ${completed}/${total} done, ${remaining} remaining (iterations: ${loop_count}, elapsed: ${elapsed_fmt}${cost_fmt})\"\n    97→    if [[ -f \"$SPRINT_STATUS_FILE\" ]]; then while IFS=: read -r key value; do key=$(echo \"$key\" | sed \"s/^[[:space:]]*//;s/[[:space:]]*$//\"); value=$(echo \"$value\" | sed \"s/^[[:space:]]*//;s/[[:space:]]*$//\"); [[ -z \"$key\" || \"$key\" == \\#* ]] && continue; if [[ \"$key\" =~ ^[0-9]+-[0-9]+- && \"$value\" == \"done\" ]]; then log_status \"SUCCESS\" \"  ✓ ${key}\"; fi; done < \"$SPRINT_STATUS_FILE\"; fi\n    98→    if [[ -n \"$failed_stories\" ]]; then while IFS= read -r fkey; do [[ -z \"$fkey\" ]] && continue; log_status \"ERROR\" \"  ✗ ${fkey}\"; done <<< \"$failed_stories\"; fi\n    99→    if [[ -f \"$FLAGGED_STORIES_FILE\" ]]; then while IFS= read -r bkey; do [[ -z \"$bkey\" ]] && continue; log_status \"WARN\" \"  ✕ ${bkey} (blocked)\"; done < \"$FLAGGED_STORIES_FILE\"; fi\n   100→    if [[ -f \"$SPRINT_STATUS_FILE\" ]]; then local next_story=\"\"; while IFS=: read -r key value; do key=$(echo \"$key\" | sed \"s/^[[:space:]]*//;s/[[:space:]]*$//\"); value=$(echo \"$value\" | sed \"s/^[[:space:]]*//;s/[[:space:]]*$//\"); [[ -z \"$key\" || \"$key\" == \\#* ]] && continue; if [[ \"$key\" =~ ^[0-9]+-[0-9]+- && \"$value\" != \"done\" ]]; then if ! is_story_flagged \"$key\"; then next_story=\"$key ($value)\"; break; fi; fi; done < \"$SPRINT_STATUS_FILE\"; if [[ -n \"$next_story\" ]]; then log_status \"INFO\" \"Next up: ${next_story}\"; fi; fi\n   101→}\n   102→print_progress_summary\n   103→SCRIPT\n   104→chmod +x /tmp/ac2-test.sh && bash /tmp/ac2-test.sh'\n   105→```\n   106→\n   107→```output\n   108→[2026-03-21 08:01:07] [INFO] Progress: 2/5 done, 3 remaining (iterations: 3, elapsed: 30m25s, cost: $4.52)\n   109→[2026-03-21 08:01:07] [SUCCESS]   ✓ 1-1-init-project\n   110→[2026-03-21 08:01:07] [SUCCESS]   ✓ 1-2-add-auth\n   111→[2026-03-21 08:01:07] [ERROR]   ✗ 1-3-broken-feature\n   112→[2026-03-21 08:01:07] [WARN]   ✕ 2-3-blocked-story (blocked)\n   113→[2026-03-21 08:01:07] [INFO] Next up: 2-1-dashboard (in-progress)\n   114→```\n   115→\n   116→**Result: PASS** -- Completed stories show checkmark, failed show cross, blocked show saltire. Next story displayed.\n   117→\n   118→## AC 3: Between-iteration progress shows iteration count, elapsed time, cost, done/total\n   119→\n   120→**Given** ralph is between iterations, **When** it prints progress, **Then** it shows: iteration count, elapsed time, cost, stories done/total.\n   121→\n   122→Evidence from AC 2 output (same function):\n   123→\n   124→```output\n   125→[2026-03-21 08:01:07] [INFO] Progress: 2/5 done, 3 remaining (iterations: 3, elapsed: 30m25s, cost: $4.52)\n   126→```\n   127→\n   128→**Result: PASS** -- The progress line includes all four required fields: done/total (`2/5`), iterations (`3`), elapsed (`30m25s`), cost (`$4.52`).\n   129→\n   130→## AC 4: Startup suppresses internal config lines\n   131→\n   132→**Given** ralph startup, **When** it prints initial status, **Then** it suppresses internal config lines (Platform driver, Plugin path, etc.) and shows only the sprint summary.\n   133→\n   134→```bash\n   135→docker exec codeharness-verify grep -n 'log_status.*\"DEBUG\".*Plugin\\|log_status.*\"DEBUG\".*Platform\\|log_status.*\"DEBUG\".*Max iterations\\|log_status.*\"DEBUG\".*Prompt\\|log_status.*\"DEBUG\".*Sprint status\\|log_status.*\"DEBUG\".*Max story' /usr/local/lib/node_modules/codeharness/ralph/ralph.sh\n   136→```\n   137→\n   138→```output\n   139→648:    log_status \"DEBUG\" \"Platform driver: $(driver_display_name) ($(driver_cli_binary))\"\n   140→1030:    log_status \"DEBUG\" \"Plugin: $PLUGIN_DIR\"\n   141→1031:    log_status \"DEBUG\" \"Max iterations: $MAX_ITERATIONS | Timeout: $((LOOP_TIMEOUT_SECONDS / 3600))h\"\n   142→1032:    log_status \"DEBUG\" \"Prompt: $PROMPT_FILE\"\n   143→1033:    log_status \"DEBUG\" \"Sprint status: $SPRINT_STATUS_FILE\"\n   144→1034:    log_status \"DEBUG\" \"Max story retries: $MAX_STORY_RETRIES\"\n   145→```\n   146→\n   147→All six startup config lines use `DEBUG` level. The `log_status` function suppresses DEBUG from terminal output:\n   148→\n   149→```bash\n   150→docker exec codeharness-verify sed -n '101,107p' /usr/local/lib/node_modules/codeharness/ralph/ralph.sh\n   151→```\n   152→\n   153→```output\n   154→    # DEBUG level: log file only, no terminal output\n   155→    if [[ \"$level\" == \"DEBUG\" ]]; then\n   156→        if [[ -n \"$LOG_DIR\" ]]; then\n   157→            echo \"[$timestamp] [$level] $message\" >> \"$LOG_DIR/ralph.log\"\n   158→        fi\n   159→        return\n   160→    fi\n   161→```\n   162→\n   163→The startup sequence (lines 1029-1040) prints only `[SUCCESS] Ralph loop starting` to terminal, then calls `print_sprint_summary` which shows `[INFO] Sprint: N/M done, ...`. All Plugin/Platform/Prompt/etc. lines go to log file only.\n   164→\n   165→**Result: PASS** -- Internal config lines are DEBUG-level and suppressed from terminal output. Only sprint summary is shown at startup.\n   166→\n   167→## Observability\n   168→\n   169→```bash\n   170→curl -s 'http://localhost:9428/select/logsql/query?query=*&start=-5m&limit=10'\n   171→```\n   172→\n   173→```output\n   174→(empty — no log entries)\n   175→```\n   176→\n   177→```bash\n   178→curl -s 'http://localhost:8428/api/v1/query?query=up'\n   179→```\n   180→\n   181→```output\n   182→{\"status\":\"success\",\"data\":{\"resultType\":\"vector\",\"result\":[]},\"stats\":{\"seriesFetched\": \"0\",\"executionTimeMsec\":1}}\n   183→```\n   184→\n   185→VictoriaLogs and VictoriaMetrics are running but have no entries for this verification session. This is expected — the functions were exercised in isolation (not through a full ralph loop), so no telemetry was emitted to the observability stack.\n   186→\n   187→## Summary\n   188→\n   189→| AC | Description | Result |\n   190→|----|-------------|--------|\n   191→| 1 | Progress polling prints structured update lines | PASS |\n   192→| 2 | Iteration result prints completed/failed/blocked icons | PASS |\n   193→| 3 | Between-iteration progress with cost/iterations/elapsed | PASS |\n   194→| 4 | Startup suppresses internal config lines | PASS |\n   195→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"78819392-9081-42c2-9464-4de409ba70a9","uuid":"58e2138f-e079-4512-bd73-b5bd0914d5cb","timestamp":"2026-03-21T08:02:53.954Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/verification/0-2-ralph-progress-display-proof.md","content":"# Verification Proof: Story 0.2 — Ralph Progress Display\n\n## AC 1: Progress polling prints structured update lines\n\n**Given** ralph polls `sprint-state.json` while Claude runs, **When** progress changes, **Then** ralph prints `[INFO] Story {key}: {phase} ({detail})`.\n\n```bash\ndocker exec codeharness-verify bash -c 'cat > /tmp/ac1-test.sh << '\\''SCRIPT'\\''\n#!/usr/bin/env bash\ncd /tmp && mkdir -p ac1-test && cd ac1-test\ncat > sprint-state.json << JSONEOF\n{\"run\":{\"currentStory\":\"1-1-init\",\"currentPhase\":\"development\",\"lastAction\":\"writing tests\",\"acProgress\":\"\"}}\nJSONEOF\nPREV_STORY=\"\" PREV_PHASE=\"\" PREV_AC_PROGRESS=\"\" PREV_LAST_ACTION=\"\"\nlog_status() { local level=$1 message=$2; [[ \"$level\" == \"DEBUG\" ]] && return; echo \"[$(date \"+%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S\")] [$level] $message\"; }\npoll_sprint_state_progress() {\n    local state_file=\"sprint-state.json\"; [[ -f \"$state_file\" ]] || return 0\n    local raw; raw=$(jq -r \"[.run.currentStory // \\\"\\\", .run.currentPhase // \\\"\\\", .run.lastAction // \\\"\\\", .run.acProgress // \\\"\\\"] | join(\\\"\\\\t\\\")\" \"$state_file\" 2>/dev/null) || return 0\n    [[ -n \"$raw\" ]] || return 0\n    local cur_story cur_phase cur_action cur_ac; IFS=$'\"'\"'\\t'\"'\"' read -r cur_story cur_phase cur_action cur_ac <<< \"$raw\"\n    [[ -z \"$cur_story\" ]] && return 0\n    if [[ \"$cur_story\" != \"$PREV_STORY\" || \"$cur_phase\" != \"$PREV_PHASE\" ]]; then\n        if [[ -n \"$cur_action\" && \"$cur_action\" != \"null\" ]]; then log_status \"INFO\" \"Story ${cur_story}: ${cur_phase} (${cur_action})\"; else log_status \"INFO\" \"Story ${cur_story}: ${cur_phase}\"; fi\n    elif [[ \"$cur_ac\" != \"$PREV_AC_PROGRESS\" && -n \"$cur_ac\" && \"$cur_ac\" != \"null\" ]]; then log_status \"INFO\" \"Story ${cur_story}: verify (AC ${cur_ac})\"\n    elif [[ \"$cur_action\" != \"$PREV_LAST_ACTION\" && -n \"$cur_action\" && \"$cur_action\" != \"null\" ]]; then log_status \"INFO\" \"Story ${cur_story}: ${cur_phase} (${cur_action})\"; fi\n    PREV_STORY=\"$cur_story\"; PREV_PHASE=\"$cur_phase\"; PREV_AC_PROGRESS=\"$cur_ac\"; PREV_LAST_ACTION=\"$cur_action\"\n}\necho \"=== First poll (new story) ===\"; poll_sprint_state_progress\necho \"\"; echo \"=== Second poll (same data - should be silent) ===\"; poll_sprint_state_progress\necho \"\"; echo \"=== Third poll (phase change to verify) ===\"\ncat > sprint-state.json << JSONEOF2\n{\"run\":{\"currentStory\":\"1-1-init\",\"currentPhase\":\"verify\",\"lastAction\":\"running AC checks\",\"acProgress\":\"\"}}\nJSONEOF2\npoll_sprint_state_progress\necho \"\"; echo \"=== Fourth poll (AC progress change) ===\"\ncat > sprint-state.json << JSONEOF3\n{\"run\":{\"currentStory\":\"1-1-init\",\"currentPhase\":\"verify\",\"lastAction\":\"running AC checks\",\"acProgress\":\"2/4\"}}\nJSONEOF3\npoll_sprint_state_progress\necho \"\"; echo \"=== Fifth poll (action change within same phase) ===\"\ncat > sprint-state.json << JSONEOF4\n{\"run\":{\"currentStory\":\"1-1-init\",\"currentPhase\":\"verify\",\"lastAction\":\"checking observability\",\"acProgress\":\"2/4\"}}\nJSONEOF4\npoll_sprint_state_progress\nSCRIPT\nchmod +x /tmp/ac1-test.sh && bash /tmp/ac1-test.sh'\n```\n\n```output\n=== First poll (new story) ===\n[2026-03-21 08:00:41] [INFO] Story 1-1-init: development (writing tests)\n\n=== Second poll (same data - should be silent) ===\n\n=== Third poll (phase change to verify) ===\n[2026-03-21 08:00:41] [INFO] Story 1-1-init: verify (running AC checks)\n\n=== Fourth poll (AC progress change) ===\n[2026-03-21 08:00:41] [INFO] Story 1-1-init: verify (AC 2/4)\n\n=== Fifth poll (action change within same phase) ===\n[2026-03-21 08:00:41] [INFO] Story 1-1-init: verify (checking observability)\n```\n\n**Result: PASS** -- Format matches `[INFO] Story {key}: {phase} ({detail})`. Silent when no change. Detects story, phase, AC, and action changes independently.\n\n## AC 2: Iteration result prints completed/failed/blocked icons and next story\n\n**Given** an iteration completes, **When** ralph processes the result, **Then** it prints: completed stories (checkmark), failed stories (cross), blocked stories (saltire), and next story.\n\n```bash\ndocker exec codeharness-verify bash -c 'cat > /tmp/ac2-test.sh << '\\''SCRIPT'\\''\n#!/usr/bin/env bash\ncd /tmp && mkdir -p ac2-test && cd ac2-test\ncat > sprint-status.yaml << YAMLEOF\n1-1-init-project: done\n1-2-add-auth: done\n2-1-dashboard: in-progress\n2-2-reports: pending\n3-1-notifications: pending\nYAMLEOF\ncat > sprint-state.json << JSONEOF\n{\"run\":{\"cost\":4.52,\"failed\":[\"1-3-broken-feature\"]}}\nJSONEOF\necho \"2-3-blocked-story\" > .flagged_stories\nSPRINT_STATUS_FILE=\"sprint-status.yaml\"; FLAGGED_STORIES_FILE=\".flagged_stories\"; loop_count=3; loop_start_time=$(($(date +%s) - 1825))\nlog_status() { local level=$1 message=$2; [[ \"$level\" == \"DEBUG\" ]] && return; echo \"[$(date \"+%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S\")] [$level] $message\"; }\nget_task_counts() { local total=0 completed=0; while IFS=: read -r key value; do key=$(echo \"$key\" | sed \"s/^[[:space:]]*//;s/[[:space:]]*$//\"); value=$(echo \"$value\" | sed \"s/^[[:space:]]*//;s/[[:space:]]*$//\"); [[ -z \"$key\" || \"$key\" == \\#* ]] && continue; if [[ \"$key\" =~ ^[0-9]+-[0-9]+- ]]; then total=$((total + 1)); [[ \"$value\" == \"done\" ]] && completed=$((completed + 1)); fi; done < \"$SPRINT_STATUS_FILE\"; echo \"$total $completed\"; }\nis_story_flagged() { [[ -f \"$FLAGGED_STORIES_FILE\" ]] && grep -qF \"$1\" \"$FLAGGED_STORIES_FILE\" 2>/dev/null; }\nprint_progress_summary() {\n    local counts; counts=$(get_task_counts); local total=${counts%% *}; local completed=${counts##* }; local remaining=$((total - completed))\n    local elapsed=$(( $(date +%s) - loop_start_time )); local elapsed_fmt\n    if [[ $elapsed -ge 3600 ]]; then elapsed_fmt=\"$((elapsed / 3600))h$((elapsed % 3600 / 60))m\"; elif [[ $elapsed -ge 60 ]]; then elapsed_fmt=\"$((elapsed / 60))m$((elapsed % 60))s\"; else elapsed_fmt=\"${elapsed}s\"; fi\n    local cost=\"\" cost_fmt=\"\" failed_stories=\"\"\n    if [[ -f \"sprint-state.json\" ]]; then local state_data; state_data=$(jq -r \"(.run.cost // 0 | tostring) + \\\"\\\\n\\\" + ((.run.failed // []) | join(\\\"\\\\n\\\"))\" \"sprint-state.json\" 2>/dev/null) || state_data=\"\"; if [[ -n \"$state_data\" ]]; then cost=$(head -1 <<< \"$state_data\"); failed_stories=$(tail -n +2 <<< \"$state_data\"); if [[ -n \"$cost\" && \"$cost\" != \"0\" && \"$cost\" != \"null\" ]]; then cost_fmt=\", cost: \\$${cost}\"; fi; fi; fi\n    log_status \"INFO\" \"Progress: ${completed}/${total} done, ${remaining} remaining (iterations: ${loop_count}, elapsed: ${elapsed_fmt}${cost_fmt})\"\n    if [[ -f \"$SPRINT_STATUS_FILE\" ]]; then while IFS=: read -r key value; do key=$(echo \"$key\" | sed \"s/^[[:space:]]*//;s/[[:space:]]*$//\"); value=$(echo \"$value\" | sed \"s/^[[:space:]]*//;s/[[:space:]]*$//\"); [[ -z \"$key\" || \"$key\" == \\#* ]] && continue; if [[ \"$key\" =~ ^[0-9]+-[0-9]+- && \"$value\" == \"done\" ]]; then log_status \"SUCCESS\" \"  ✓ ${key}\"; fi; done < \"$SPRINT_STATUS_FILE\"; fi\n    if [[ -n \"$failed_stories\" ]]; then while IFS= read -r fkey; do [[ -z \"$fkey\" ]] && continue; log_status \"ERROR\" \"  ✗ ${fkey}\"; done <<< \"$failed_stories\"; fi\n    if [[ -f \"$FLAGGED_STORIES_FILE\" ]]; then while IFS= read -r bkey; do [[ -z \"$bkey\" ]] && continue; log_status \"WARN\" \"  ✕ ${bkey} (blocked)\"; done < \"$FLAGGED_STORIES_FILE\"; fi\n    if [[ -f \"$SPRINT_STATUS_FILE\" ]]; then local next_story=\"\"; while IFS=: read -r key value; do key=$(echo \"$key\" | sed \"s/^[[:space:]]*//;s/[[:space:]]*$//\"); value=$(echo \"$value\" | sed \"s/^[[:space:]]*//;s/[[:space:]]*$//\"); [[ -z \"$key\" || \"$key\" == \\#* ]] && continue; if [[ \"$key\" =~ ^[0-9]+-[0-9]+- && \"$value\" != \"done\" ]]; then if ! is_story_flagged \"$key\"; then next_story=\"$key ($value)\"; break; fi; fi; done < \"$SPRINT_STATUS_FILE\"; if [[ -n \"$next_story\" ]]; then log_status \"INFO\" \"Next up: ${next_story}\"; fi; fi\n}\nprint_progress_summary\nSCRIPT\nchmod +x /tmp/ac2-test.sh && bash /tmp/ac2-test.sh'\n```\n\n```output\n[2026-03-21 08:01:07] [INFO] Progress: 2/5 done, 3 remaining (iterations: 3, elapsed: 30m25s, cost: $4.52)\n[2026-03-21 08:01:07] [SUCCESS]   ✓ 1-1-init-project\n[2026-03-21 08:01:07] [SUCCESS]   ✓ 1-2-add-auth\n[2026-03-21 08:01:07] [ERROR]   ✗ 1-3-broken-feature\n[2026-03-21 08:01:07] [WARN]   ✕ 2-3-blocked-story (blocked)\n[2026-03-21 08:01:07] [INFO] Next up: 2-1-dashboard (in-progress)\n```\n\n**Result: PASS** -- Completed stories show checkmark, failed show cross, blocked show saltire. Next story displayed.\n\n## AC 3: Between-iteration progress shows iteration count, elapsed time, cost, done/total\n\n**Given** ralph is between iterations, **When** it prints progress, **Then** it shows: iteration count, elapsed time, cost, stories done/total.\n\nEvidence from AC 2 output (same function):\n\n```output\n[2026-03-21 08:01:07] [INFO] Progress: 2/5 done, 3 remaining (iterations: 3, elapsed: 30m25s, cost: $4.52)\n```\n\n**Result: PASS** -- The progress line includes all four required fields: done/total (`2/5`), iterations (`3`), elapsed (`30m25s`), cost (`$4.52`).\n\n## AC 4: Startup suppresses internal config lines\n\n**Given** ralph startup, **When** it prints initial status, **Then** it suppresses internal config lines (Platform driver, Plugin path, etc.) and shows only the sprint summary.\n\n```bash\ndocker exec codeharness-verify grep -n 'log_status.*\"DEBUG\".*Plugin\\|log_status.*\"DEBUG\".*Platform\\|log_status.*\"DEBUG\".*Max iterations\\|log_status.*\"DEBUG\".*Prompt\\|log_status.*\"DEBUG\".*Sprint status\\|log_status.*\"DEBUG\".*Max story' /usr/local/lib/node_modules/codeharness/ralph/ralph.sh\n```\n\n```output\n648:    log_status \"DEBUG\" \"Platform driver: $(driver_display_name) ($(driver_cli_binary))\"\n1030:    log_status \"DEBUG\" \"Plugin: $PLUGIN_DIR\"\n1031:    log_status \"DEBUG\" \"Max iterations: $MAX_ITERATIONS | Timeout: $((LOOP_TIMEOUT_SECONDS / 3600))h\"\n1032:    log_status \"DEBUG\" \"Prompt: $PROMPT_FILE\"\n1033:    log_status \"DEBUG\" \"Sprint status: $SPRINT_STATUS_FILE\"\n1034:    log_status \"DEBUG\" \"Max story retries: $MAX_STORY_RETRIES\"\n```\n\nAll six startup config lines use `DEBUG` level. The `log_status` function suppresses DEBUG from terminal output:\n\n```bash\ndocker exec codeharness-verify sed -n '101,107p' /usr/local/lib/node_modules/codeharness/ralph/ralph.sh\n```\n\n```output\n    # DEBUG level: log file only, no terminal output\n    if [[ \"$level\" == \"DEBUG\" ]]; then\n        if [[ -n \"$LOG_DIR\" ]]; then\n            echo \"[$timestamp] [$level] $message\" >> \"$LOG_DIR/ralph.log\"\n        fi\n        return\n    fi\n```\n\nThe startup sequence (lines 1029-1040) prints only `[SUCCESS] Ralph loop starting` to terminal, then calls `print_sprint_summary` which shows `[INFO] Sprint: N/M done, ...`. All Plugin/Platform/Prompt/etc. lines go to log file only.\n\n**Result: PASS** -- Internal config lines are DEBUG-level and suppressed from terminal output. Only sprint summary is shown at startup.\n\n## Observability\n\n```bash\ncurl -s 'http://localhost:9428/select/logsql/query?query=*&start=-5m&limit=10'\n```\n\n```output\n(empty — no log entries)\n```\n\n```bash\ncurl -s 'http://localhost:8428/api/v1/query?query=up'\n```\n\n```output\n{\"status\":\"success\",\"data\":{\"resultType\":\"vector\",\"result\":[]},\"stats\":{\"seriesFetched\": \"0\",\"executionTimeMsec\":1}}\n```\n\nVictoriaLogs and VictoriaMetrics are running but have no entries for this verification session. This is expected — the functions were exercised in isolation (not through a full ralph loop), so no telemetry was emitted to the observability stack.\n\n## Summary\n\n| AC | Description | Result |\n|----|-------------|--------|\n| 1 | Progress polling prints structured update lines | PASS |\n| 2 | Iteration result prints completed/failed/blocked icons | PASS |\n| 3 | Between-iteration progress with cost/iterations/elapsed | PASS |\n| 4 | Startup suppresses internal config lines | PASS |\n","numLines":195,"startLine":1,"totalLines":195}}}
