{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"You are a black-box verifier. Verify story 0-3-run-command-dashboard.\n\nWorking directory: /tmp/codeharness-verify-0-3-run-command-dashboard\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n1. **Given** `codeharness run` starts, **When** output is displayed, **Then** it shows: sprint summary (done/remaining), current story, phase — not raw ralph debug/info lines.\n2. **Given** ralph prints a story completion line, **When** the dashboard displays it, **Then** format is: `✓ Story {key}: DONE ({duration}, ${cost})`.\n3. **Given** ralph prints a failure, **When** displayed, **Then** format is: `✗ Story {key}: FAIL at AC {n} — {one-line error}`.\n4. **Given** `--quiet` flag, **When** run starts, **Then** all output is suppressed (background mode).\n5. **Given** no `--quiet` flag, **When** ralph is running Claude, **Then** dashboard shows: `◆ {story_key} — {phase} (elapsed {time})` updating every 10 seconds.\n\n## How to Verify\n\nThis story adds a `DashboardFormatter` class and integrates it into `codeharness run`. The CLI is a Node.js tool installed globally in the container.\n\nALL commands via `docker exec codeharness-verify ...`\n\n**AC1:** Check that `codeharness run --help` shows the command exists. Then verify the DashboardFormatter filters ralph output by testing it with mock input. Try: `docker exec codeharness-verify node -e \"...\"` to exercise any exported formatter. Or check if run.ts has the dashboard integration by examining the installed package.\n\n**AC2 & AC3:** Exercise the DashboardFormatter directly. The dist/ bundle has the formatter compiled in. Try:\n- `docker exec codeharness-verify node -e \"const m = require('codeharness'); console.log(Object.keys(m))\"` to see exports\n- Or look for the dashboard-formatter module in the installed package\n\n**AC4:** Verify `--quiet` flag: `docker exec codeharness-verify codeharness run --help` should show --quiet option.\n\n**AC5:** Verify ticker line format by exercising getTickerLine().\n\nIf you can't import the formatter directly (tree-shaking), verify by:\n1. Checking the compiled JS in the container for DashboardFormatter class\n2. Running `codeharness run --help` to confirm the command exists with proper flags\n3. Using `node -e` to load and test any accessible exports\n\n### Observability\nAfter each docker exec, check: `curl 'http://localhost:9428/select/logsql/query?query=*&start=-30s&limit=100'`\n\n## Write Proof\n\nWrite to: `verification/0-3-run-command-dashboard-proof.md`\n\nEach AC must have a `## AC N: description` heading, a ```bash block with `docker exec`, and an ```output block with results. Only use `bash` and `output` fence languages.\n\n## Rules\n1. ALL commands via `docker exec codeharness-verify ...`\n2. Report REAL failures\n3. Every AC needs functional evidence\n4. [ESCALATE] only for genuinely impossible things\n5. Never switch to unit-testable verification\n\nEnd with `## Session Issues` section."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_014avHDXSqNtDprZdVEAoxod","session_id":"78819392-9081-42c2-9464-4de409ba70a9","uuid":"6d353c5b-9762-4e85-8971-d966f96ed026","timestamp":"2026-03-21T08:04:12.555Z"}
